# Documentation and Maintenance Rule

- Whenever a critical functionality change is made, update all relevant maintenance files:
  - `README.md`
  - `src/genesis/instruments/DRIVER_AUTHORING_GUIDE.md`
- Keep `.gitignore` up to date for any new generated artifacts, caches, logs, local tooling outputs, or other non-source files introduced by the change.
- Include user-facing behavior changes, operational workflow updates, and any driver-impacting runtime/safety changes.
- Before finishing work, verify these files are still accurate for the new behavior.
- After every edit batch, run pre-commit (`pre-commit run --all-files`) and fix issues before handing off or finishing.
- When providing a context handoff/summary for the next agent, explicitly include:
  - whether `README.md`, `src/genesis/instruments/DRIVER_AUTHORING_GUIDE.md`, and `.gitignore` were reviewed/updated,
  - what sections changed,
  - confirmation that pre-commit was run after edits,
  - and any pending maintenance follow-ups.
